Rash Driving
Analyser using ML &
Deep Learning
142219104126 - Sreejith S
142219104135 - Syed Anas Ahmed
142219104142 - Yuvankumar R
ABSTRACT
The proposed project presents a system that detects close calls while driving and predicts
the future driving of the driver using machine learning and deep learning techniques. The
system uses IoT devices to collect data about the driving conditions, such as the speed and
distance of nearby vehicles, and the location of the vehicle using a GPS module. The
collected data is then transmitted to the backend server using a POST API, in the form of a
JSON data packet. The system uses a Random Forest algorithm to determine whether a
close call has occurred or not, based on the input data from the IoT devices. An RNN
algorithm is used to predict the future driving behavior of the driver, based on the historical
data of the driving conditions. The system is designed to be used with a web application and
an Android application, which can display the close call data and the predictions in a chart
format.
INTRODUCTION
The increasing number of road accidents due to reckless driving has become a major
concern worldwide. To address this issue, we propose a Rash Driving Analyzer using
Machine Learning and Deep Learning to detect close calls and predict future driving
behavior.
The system uses IoT devices to detect the speed and distance of nearby vehicles, along
with a GPS module to determine the current location. The collected data is analyzed
using Random Forest and Recurrent Neural Network algorithms to determine whether a
close call has been made and to predict future driving behavior.
A dataset is used to train both models. The system is implemented as a web and
Android application, with an easy-to-use interface for close call reports and prediction
charts. The system architecture is designed to enable easy data transfer from IoT
devices to the backend server.

EXISTING SYSTEM
Driving behavior monitoring systems have been implemented using various techniques
such as
Manual reporting
Video analysis
Sensor-based approaches.
Manual reporting is an unreliable and time-consuming process.
Video analysis is intrusive and can be prohibitively expensive.
Sensor-based approaches, although effective, are expensive to maintain and can suffer
from high false positive rates. These limitations make it challenging to deploy driving
behavior monitoring systems on a large scale.
Moreover, these systems do not provide real-time feedback, making it difficult for
drivers to identify and correct their driving behavior. Therefore, there is a need for a
reliable, cost-effective, and efficient driving behavior monitoring system that can
provide real-time feedback and enable drivers to take corrective action when necessary.
PROPOSED SYSTEM
The proposed system is aRash Driving Analyzer that uses IoT devices, such as IR and
ultrasonic sensors, and a GPS module to detect close calls and predict future driving
behavior.
The system uses Random Forest and Recurrent Neural Network algorithms to analyze
the data collected by the IoT devices and provide real-time feedback to the driver.
The proposed system is :
Cost-effective
Efficient
Provides real-time predictions, enabling drivers to avoid dangerous maneuvers
Reduce the risk of accidents caused by reckless driving
The system is implemented as a web and Android application, providing easy-to-use
interfaces for close call reports and prediction charts.
SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
The proposed system consists of two main components:
IoT devices
Backend server
MODULES
Data collection module: This module collects data on driving conditions using IoT
devices, such as IR sensors, Ultrasonic sensors, and GPS modules.
Data processing module: This module processes the collected data and prepares it for
analysis.
Close call detection module: This module uses a Random Forest algorithm to detect
close calls while driving, based on the input data from the IoT devices.
Future driving prediction module: This module uses an RNN algorithm to predict the
future driving behavior of the driver, based on historical data of the driving conditions.
User interface module: This module provides a user interface for displaying the close
call data and the predictions in a chart format.

ALGORITHMS
Random Forest Classifier:
Random Forest is one of the most popular and commonly used algorithm. Random
forest is a Supervised Machine Learning Algorithm that is used widely in Classification
and Regression problems.
It builds decision trees on different samples and takes their majority vote for
classification and average in case of regression.
Recurrent Neural Network(RNN) LSTM
RNN works on the principle of saving the output of a particular layer and feeding this
back to the input in order to predict the output of the layer.
LSTMs ( Long Short-Term Memory ) are a special kind of RNN capable of learning
long-term dependencies by remembering information for long periods is the default
behavior.
IMPLEMENTATION
To implement the proposed system, a hardware device consisting of aGPS module,
an IR sensor, Ultra Sonic Sensor, and a microcontroller was developed to collect and
process real-time driving data.
The collected data was transmitted to a cloud-based server using a WIFI network,
where a machine learning algorithm was deployed to classify the driving behavior as
normal or aggressive.
The developed algorithm will be trained on a large dataset of labeled driving data, and
expected to achieve a high accuracy of 95%in detecting aggressive driving behavior.
An Android mobile application was also developed to provide real-time feedback to
drivers on their driving behavior and to alert them in case of detected aggressive
driving behavior.
CONCLUSION
In conclusion, the proposed Rash Driving Analyzer system effectively detects close calls
and predicts future driving behavior using IoT devices and machine learning algorithms.
The system provides real-time feedback to drivers, allowing them to take corrective
action and reduce the risk of accidents caused by reckless driving. The use of Random
Forest and Recurrent Neural Network algorithms results in accurate predictions and
high performance.
The proposed system's architecture and modules are designed to be cost-effective,
efficient, and scalable, making it a viable solution for large-scale deployment. The web
and android applications provide users with a user-friendly interface for visualizing the
close calls and the driving behavior predictions.
